
Overview of noun gleam

The noun gleam has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (3) gleam, gleaming, glow, lambency -- (an appearance of reflected light)
2. (2) gleam, gleaming, glimmer -- (a flash of light (especially reflected light))

Overview of verb gleam

The verb gleam has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (3) glitter, glisten, glint, gleam, shine -- (be shiny, as if wet; "His eyes were glistening")
2. (3) gleam, glimmer -- (shine brightly, like a star or a light)
3. (1) gleam -- (appear briefly; "A terrible thought gleamed in her mind")
